				\begin{document}$$ V \ge E $$\end{document}V≥E. Over time, the fleet size (V) and the fishing effort (E) follow different paths in different fishing ports and for the two types of fleets. The Shannon function H is used as a fleet diversity index (Eide 2016), mapping how fleet diversity develops in the different simulations.
